## Vercel Speed Insights Installation - Status Report

### Summary
Vercel Speed Insights is already installed and properly configured in this Next.js project. The implementation follows the latest official documentation from Vercel.

### Current Configuration

**Package Installation:**
- ✅ Package `@vercel/speed-insights` (version ^2.0.0) is present in `package.json`
- ✅ Package lock file (`package-lock.json`) is up to date

**Implementation:**
- ✅ SpeedInsights component imported from `@vercel/speed-insights/next` (Next.js-specific entry point)
- ✅ Component placed in root layout at `app/layout.tsx`
- ✅ Component correctly positioned at the end of the `<body>` tag

**Verification:**
- ✅ Build completes successfully without errors
- ✅ TypeScript compilation passes
- ✅ All pages generate correctly (4 routes: /, /_not-found, /oferta)

### Implementation Details

**File: `linhao_front/app/layout.tsx`**
The SpeedInsights component is correctly integrated:
```typescript
import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'

export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <html lang="ru" className="scroll-smooth">
      <body className={`${racama.variable} `}>
        {children}
        <SpeedInsights />
      </body>
    </html>
  )
}
```

### Documentation Reference
Installation instructions were verified against the official Vercel documentation:
- Package: `@vercel/speed-insights`
- Import: `@vercel/speed-insights/next` (for Next.js v13.5+)
- Placement: End of `<body>` tag in root layout

### Notes
- The previous pull request (#1) successfully installed and configured Speed Insights
- No changes were required as the implementation already follows current best practices
- The project is ready to collect Speed Insights data when deployed to Vercel
- Speed Insights must be enabled in the Vercel dashboard to start collecting metrics

### Next Steps
To start collecting Speed Insights data:
1. Enable Speed Insights in your Vercel project dashboard
2. Deploy the project to Vercel (via `vercel deploy` or Git integration)
3. Speed Insights will automatically begin tracking Core Web Vitals and performance metrics
